---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const snapshot = [
  { label: "Industry", value: "Fintech / Enterprise Platform" },
  { label: "Role", value: "UX Design Consultant" },
  { label: "Scope", value: "Global platform, cross-market servicing workflows" },
  { label: "Focus", value: "Usability, workflow clarity, system consistency" },
];

const decisions = [
  {
    title: "Workflow-first design",
    text: "We prioritized end-to-end servicing workflows over isolated screens, ensuring users could complete tasks more efficiently across the system.",
  },
  {
    title: "Consistency through shared patterns",
    text: "We introduced consistent interaction patterns and design standards to reduce cognitive load and improve usability across regions.",
  },
  {
    title: "Localization with structural integrity",
    text: "We balanced global consistency with local market needs, ensuring the platform could scale without fragmentation.",
  },
];

const outcomes = [
  "Simplified complex servicing workflows to reduce friction and improve usability across the platform.",
  "Increased consistency across platform experiences through shared interaction patterns and design standards.",
  "Strengthened the UX foundation for scalable product development across global markets.",
  "Enabled clearer alignment between design, product, and engineering teams.",
];
---

<MainLayout title="Global Servicing Platform | Jorge Obando">
  <section class="case-study-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">American Express</p>
        <h1>Global Servicing Platform</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Improving a large-scale enterprise platform by simplifying workflows,
          strengthening UX foundations, and creating a more consistent system across
          global servicing operations.
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="hero-image">
        <img src="/images/American Express.jpg" alt="American Express global servicing platform case study visual" />
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="snapshot-grid" aria-label="Case study snapshot">
      {snapshot.map((item) => (
        <article class="snapshot-card">
          <p class="snapshot-label">{item.label}</p>
          <p class="snapshot-value">{item.value}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The situation</h2>
      <p>
        The platform supported complex servicing operations across multiple regions,
        but the experience was fragmented. Inconsistent interaction patterns and
        disconnected workflows increased cognitive load and made work less efficient.
      </p>
      <p>
        As the platform expanded globally, those inconsistencies made it harder to
        maintain quality, scale effectively, and deliver a cohesive user experience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The challenge</h2>
      <p>
        The challenge was to improve usability and consistency across a large,
        distributed system while supporting diverse workflows across regions and
        user types.
      </p>
      <p>
        This required aligning design patterns, simplifying workflows, and building
        a stronger UX foundation that could scale without adding more complexity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p>
        As a UX Design Consultant, I worked across product, engineering, and design
        teams to improve the overall platform experience. I contributed to both
        strategy and execution, helping define workflows, patterns, and interaction
        models.
      </p>
      <p>
        My focus was reducing fragmentation and improving how the system worked as a
        whole rather than optimizing screens in isolation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>How I operated</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid two-up">
        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Identified system-level issues</h3>
          <p>
            We analyzed workflows across the platform to uncover inconsistencies,
            redundancies, and high-friction moments.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Established UX foundations</h3>
          <p>
            We introduced shared patterns and principles that improved consistency
            and usability across the system.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Aligned teams</h3>
          <p>
            I worked with cross-functional teams to ensure design decisions were
            understood, implemented, and applied consistently across products.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Improved execution quality</h3>
          <p>
            We strengthened the connection between design and engineering, reducing
            ambiguity and improving delivery quality.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Key decisions</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid one-up">
        {decisions.map((item) => (
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>{item.title}</h3>
            <p>{item.text}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Outcomes</h2>
      <div class="outcomes-card">
        <ul>
          {outcomes.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Reflection</h2>
      <p>
        This work reinforced the importance of strong UX foundations in enterprise
        systems. Improving consistency and workflow clarity at the system level
        creates lasting value well beyond any single feature.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Related Thinking</h2>
      <section class="article-links" aria-label="Related thinking and next navigation">
        <a href="/thinking/measuring-what-matters">
          Why measuring outcomes—not outputs—changes how systems improve
        </a>
        <a href="/thinking/governed-product-system">
          Designing governed product systems for scale, consistency, and alignment
        </a>
        <a href="/case-studies">
          Return to all case studies
        </a>
      </section>
    </section>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .case-study-page {
    padding: 2.5rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(320px, 0.9fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: end;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .hero-copy {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #a33a3a;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 4vw, 4.15rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .lead {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #555;
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .hero-image {
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--divider);
    border-radius: 18px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .hero-image img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    min-height: 280px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .snapshot-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .snapshot-card,
  .info-card,
  .outcomes-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--divider);
    border-radius: 16px;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .snapshot-card {
    padding: 1.2rem;
  }

  .snapshot-label {
    margin: 0 0 0.45rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #777;
  }

  .snapshot-value {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #222;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--divider);
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 2.2vw, 2.4rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  }

  .content-section p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  .cards-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .cards-grid.two-up {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .cards-grid.one-up {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .info-card {
    padding: 1.4rem;
  }

  .info-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .info-card p {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .outcomes-card {
    padding: 1.35rem 1.4rem;
  }

  .outcomes-card ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  .outcomes-card li {
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #444;
  }

  .outcomes-card li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .article-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--divider);
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .article-links a {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #111;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .hero {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .snapshot-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .case-study-page {
      padding: 1.5rem 0 4rem;
    }

    .snapshot-grid,
    .cards-grid.two-up {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 1.02rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
    }

    .hero-image img {
      min-height: 220px;
    }

    .article-links {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.35rem;
    }
  }
</style>